    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0327"/>
        		<head>Jim to Mademoiselle Marcelle Guerin <date value="1916-05-19">May 19th 1916</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-05-19">May 19th 1916</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Marcelle:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            We have just
            received orders to go to
            Verdun, and are leaving
            to morrow.  I broke two
            longerous in my machine 
            on landing and so will 
            fly an extra one up and 
            come back for mine later.
            </p><p>
            Kiffin got a Boche
            yesterday.  He saw him
            over Thaun [sp?] and dove.  The 
            Boche began shooting when
            he was a 1,000 meters
            off.  Kiffin didn’t fire
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0329" n="[p.2]"/>
            
            until within 30 meters.  He
            saw the mitrailleur fall
            back against the pilot
            and the pilot flopp [sic] to
            one side.  The machine
            fell in a cloud of smoke
            and Kiffin saw it burning
            on the ground just
            back of the German lines.
            The Boches got peeved and
            so came over this morning
            and dropped bombs on us
            which did not damage.
            Bill Thaw had a fight
            the day before.  He thought
            </p><p>
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0328" n="[p.3]"/>
            
            he had missed him but
            an artillery observer phoned
            in he had seen it
            hic straight for the 
            ground.  I haven’t been able
            to fly for the past
            three days because the 
            cuckoo is busted.
            </p><p>
            Keep an eye out 
            for the moving pictures 
            of the outfit.  They 
            will, I think, be 
            shown in Paris.
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0330" n="[p.4]"/>
            
            There is no other
            news of interest save
            that Cowden is still
            in Paris and Prince
            busted up en route here.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>My best</salute>
            
            <signed>Jim</signed>
            
            <seg type="postscript">
            Escadrille N. 124<lb/>
            B.C.M.<lb/>
            Paris.
            </seg>
        		</closer>
        		
